('Finance & Operations', 'Lead Your Company, Lead Your World', '<p>Leadership is the art of getting work done through others. However, it can sometimes be difficult to lead your team to your desired outcome.&nbsp; Things get in the way&mdash;personal agendas, company cultures, the inability to make difficult decisions.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wright explores how leadership evolves as your company grows.&nbsp; In his presentation, he discusses how leaders deal with different personalities, get the most from the lease, build a culture, and become a trusted advisor.&nbsp; He also talks about some of the most common errors that small business leaders face.<br />&nbsp;To assist entrepreneurs in leading their organization, Dr. Bob discusses a methodology called the ideal state planning process&mdash;a powerful tool of visioning and alignment that helps build a fulfilling team culture and assists in conflict management and resolution.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to also look over the articles from our featured experts Rieva Lesonsky and Stever Robbins. Rieva discusses the need for leadership in the start-up scenario and Stever writes about the need for leaders to fire things up during tough times.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Take some time to assess your leadership challenges.</p>', 'http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/2180310?rel=0'),
