('Marketing', 'The Truth Be Told', '<p><strong>Note:</strong>Core Webinar 1, June 2, 2011 Taking a Closer Look; start at 4:20</p>\r\n<p>In order to understand the real benefit of what you offer your customers, you need to ask them. In this chapter, Michelle Lanter Smith will walk you through how you take your customers&rsquo; responses from your <em>Voice of the Customer</em> surveys and create your business identity.&nbsp; Your business identity is like a bumper sticker for your company.&nbsp; A concise and clear statement, it communicates your one key benefit that positions your business and differentiates you from your competition. It all starts with asking your customers about your strengths and weaknesses and how they benefit from your product or service.&nbsp; Upon completion of your business identity, you can easily springboard to the core messages that you want to include in your marketing communications planning.</p>\r\n<p>To get the most from this chapter, be sure to download the business identity worksheet prior to listening to the webinar.&nbsp; Then, read the articles to learn why you need to focus your business message and why you must focus on the benefits you deliver to your customers and not lose sight of them amongst your daily trials and tribulations.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Determine your business&rsquo; sweet spot--complete your business identity worksheet.</p>', 'https://amfam.webex.com/amfam/lsr.php?AT=pb&SP=EC&rID=42939477&rKey=993ebce29dc462c4 '),
