('Marketing', 'Sticky Marketing', '<p><strong>Note:</strong> 2011, Core Webinar 3-- Sticky Business; start at 2:45</p>\r\n<p>Before you can get your marketing messages out, you need to build a plan.&nbsp; This chapter features a webinar with Michelle Lanter Smith in which she reviews a simple, yet effective marketing plan template that you can use to build your small business&rsquo; marketing plan.&nbsp; She discusses how you can select the right tactics to meet your objectives and how you can get your year&rsquo;s plan all down on an easy-to-use excel template.</p>\r\n<p>Also in this chapter&rsquo;s webinar, Barbara Lopez will teach you how to craft a message that you&rsquo;ll use to introduce your business.&nbsp; This is something that you&rsquo;ll communicate day in and day out to position your business properly and attract potential customers.&nbsp; Barbara will take you through her F.A.R.M. system&mdash;four easy steps to building your elevator pitch.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, your marketing plan should not just be about finding new customers.&nbsp; Read this chapter&rsquo;s articles to help you renew your focus on your current customer base.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Complete your marketing plan; download the marketing plan worksheet.</p>', 'https://amfam.webex.com/amfam/lsr.php?AT=pb&SP=EC&rID=43195317&rKey=ef217fa3db532f41 '),
('Marketing', 'Sticky Marketing', '<p><strong>Note:</strong> 2011, Core Webinar 3-- Sticky Business; start at 2:45</p>\r\n<p>Before you can get your marketing messages out, you need to build a plan.&nbsp; This chapter features a webinar with Michelle Lanter Smith in which she reviews a simple, yet effective marketing plan template that you can use to build your small business&rsquo; marketing plan.&nbsp; She discusses how you can select the right tactics to meet your objectives and how you can get your year&rsquo;s plan all down on an easy-to-use excel template.</p>\r\n<p>Also in this chapter&rsquo;s webinar, Barbara Lopez will teach you how to craft a message that you&rsquo;ll use to introduce your business.&nbsp; This is something that you&rsquo;ll communicate day in and day out to position your business properly and attract potential customers.&nbsp; Barbara will take you through her F.A.R.M. system&mdash;four easy steps to building your elevator pitch.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, your marketing plan should not just be about finding new customers.&nbsp; Read this chapter&rsquo;s articles to help you renew your focus on your current customer base.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Complete your marketing plan; download the marketing plan worksheet.</p>', 'https://amfam.webex.com/amfam/lsr.php?AT=pb&SP=EC&rID=43195317&rKey=ef217fa3db532f41 '),
('Sales', 'Marketing on a Limited Budget', '<p><strong>Note:</strong> Core Webinar 4, July 14, 2011; start at 2:16</p>\r\n<p>Some people think that the word marketing equates to &ldquo;money&rdquo; . . . that is, spending lots of it.&nbsp; But that&rsquo;s not necessarily the case.&nbsp; In this chapter, we&rsquo;ll discuss in the webinar and the articles some of the most popular e-marketing tools such as newsletters, blogging, and social media.&nbsp; In addition, we&rsquo;ll also dive deep into some really great word-of-mouth techniques that give people something to talk about.&nbsp;&nbsp; Bottom line: if your business can devise customer experiences that are memorable and out of the ordinary, you are more likely to get customers to talk about you.</p>\r\n<p>Michelle Lanter Smith will moderate a discussion with social media gurus Dean DeLisle and Jeannie Walters on how to use some of these effective small business marketing tools.&nbsp; Also, John Jantsch will give you some excellent tips on leveraging social media to market your small business.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Set aside 20 minutes a day to do your social media outreach.</p>', 'https://amfam.webex.com/amfam/lsr.php?AT=pb&SP=EC&rID=43331272&rKey=36b8513f3a4a5a73 '),
